@Welhung

No one is confusing Latin with Spanish. Latin Spanish and Castilian Spanish are different dialects. If you speak one, you can understand the other fairly well. However, they do not share complete vocabularies and some words in one exist as different words in another, creating some difficulties in cross-dialect communication.

Latin Spanish is spoken mostly in Latin America (notice the word Latin used in both) and Castilian Spanish is spoken largely in Northern and Central Spain.
